com.chrismin13.additionsapi.items

Class CustomItemStack

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.chrismin13.additionsapi.items.CustomItemStack
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable

    public class CustomItemStack
extends Object
implements Cloneable
    A CustomItemStack contains an ItemStack and a Custom Item. Especially useful if you want to get the ItemStack of a Custom Item or vice versa.
    Author:
    chrismin13

    • Method Detail

      • getCustomItem

        public CustomItem getCustomItem()
        Returns:
        The CustomItem that is contained in the CustomItemStack.

      • getTexture

        public String getTexture()
        Returns:
        The texture of the Custom Item. If the Custom Item does not implement ModelInjector (in other words, it's not a CustomTexturedItem or similar and does not contain a Texture) it will return null.

      • setTexture

        public CustomItemStack setTexture(String texture)
        Sets the Texture of the ItemStack. This is only applicable for CustomItems that implement ModelInjector and have the Texture already Initialized with the AdditionsAPIInitializationEvent.
        When the Texture is set, the ItemStack's durability is changed according to the data file.
        Parameters:
        texture - The name of the Texture.

      • getItemStack

        public org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack getItemStack()
        Returns:
        The ItemStack that the CustomItemStack contains.

      • getFakeDurability

        public int getFakeDurability()
        Returns:
        The Fake Durability of the ItemStack. This is only valid if the CustomItem has Fake Durability. If it does not, it will return 0.

      • getMaxFakeDurability

        public int getMaxFakeDurability()
        Returns:
        int - The maximum fake durability of the CustomItem. If this is above 0, then the Fake Durability lore is enabled. The fake durability lore offers a near perfect recreation of the Minecraft durability mechanics but hidden in the lore. This way, Textured Items that have to be unbreakable can still have durability mechanics.

      • setFakeDurability

        public CustomItemStack setFakeDurability(int durability)
        Sets the ItemStack's Current Fake Durability. This is only valid of the CustomItem has Fake Durability.
        Parameters:
        durability - The durability to set.

      • reduceDurability

        public CustomItemStack reduceDurability(org.bukkit.entity.Player player,
                                        int durabilityToReduce)
        Reduces the durability of the CustomItemStack, whether it's using Fake Durability or not. It uses the PlayerCustomItemDamageEvent, so it could be cancelled.
        Parameters:
        durabilityToReduce - The amount of durability that will be reduced

      • updateLore

        public CustomItemStack updateLore()
        Updates the lore of the ItemStack using the CustomItem.getFullLore(Map, int, Attributes) method. This is necessary if you added Enchantments and will be done automatically if the Item was enchanted in an enchantment table or had its durability changed.

      • updateLore

        public CustomItemStack updateLore(Map<org.bukkit.enchantments.Enchantment,Integer> enchantsToCheck)
        Updates the lore of the ItemStack using the CustomItem.getFullLore(Map, int, Attributes) method. This is necessary if you added Enchantments and will be done automatically if the Item was enchanted in an enchantment table or had its durability changed.

        public void addAllNBTData(Map<? extends String,? extends Object> nbtData)
